values:
We're in Victoria, and we're so bored right now.

In Montreal we would have found something to do even if we didn't have plans...but in Victoria where we have no friends, we don't have anything to do.  

We've called all our friends (old school friends of mine and Montreal->Victoria friends) here, and everyone's out...and if they're in, they're doing something else.

Vive la last minute party...but where are you?!?

BooHoo
x
Suzie

You Belong in 1956
If you scored... 1950 - 1959: You're fun loving, romantic, and more than a little innocent. See you at the drive in! 1960 - 1969: You are a free spirit with a huge heart. Love, peace, and happiness rule - oh, and drugs too. 1970 - 1979: Bold and brash, you take life by the horns. Whether you're partying or protesting, you give it your all! 1980 - 1989: Wild, over the top, and just a little bit cheesy. You're colorful at night - and successful during the day. 1990 - 1999: With you anything goes! You're grunge one day, ghetto fabulous the next. It's all good!
What Year Do You Belong In?

ninja wisdom:

"Wearing black eyeliner is good for blending in with the environments. Especially good for public missions where photo ops may arise. Don't forget to wear your mask."

you knew we were ninja's right?

Ah yes, the throngs of emails and letters and congratulations of all kinds keep rolling in...and I of course mean because of my darling and my engagement..and the fact that we've made it this far without having to duke it out.  Haha..

I'm happy that I have friends...here in Montreal, and in Victoria, and all over the world, it seems.  I'm happy that I know who they are, or at least am finding out.

It's so weird...I've been getting congrats from people that I didn't even know were my friends..and loving it.  Ex-girlfriends, ex-boyfriends, people I met on the internet.  All cause for celebration!  Yipeeeeeeeeeeeeee....

Good thing I sprinkled lithium on my Special K today!  Haha...

The more I read, the more I want to write.  Take now for example...I want to write about my life because I'm reading a book where the character (one anyway) is writing a work of fiction based on her own experiences.  The other two characters are involved in the literary world as well, one being an already published author and the other is a literary agent.  This doesn't really matter as it's Gemma who's inspired me a little...or is it Marion Keyes?  Hmmm...

Anyway, I was walking up the stairs to work (it is intirely possible that the impending doom of having to slug it out for 5 hours shelving manky library books has inspired this creative outburst) and wondering if I'd ever been "ridey."

Apparently...if you look at my last journal entry, which I was going to erase.  Haha..

Yes, so have I ever been "ridey" ? ? ?

Not today, obviously, I'm wearing a pair of flaming bowling shoes, rolled up jeans that I just a bit too tight, a pirate shirt with my signature cut down the front..and pigtails.  More cute, less ridey (I've decided to use the word now with out the " " - you do understand what it means, don't you?).

Let's go through my history.

1993 - Ridey, but taken.

1994 - More ridey, but still taken.

1995 - Even more ridey, and enjoying it.

1996 - Ridey, but only for foreigners.

1997 - Agressively ridey, especially in Ireland.

1998 - Ridey, but wanting to find someone to share it with.

1999 - 2003 - Internet ridey.  Then real life ridey for one man.

2003 - Present - Not entirely, but nearly.

Hahahahahahaha...

Ah, shit.  I've got to get to work.  Time to put my nose to the grindstone.

x
Suzie

Is it because he's a boy..and sort of slutty in the LiveJournal department? Hmmmm.. Here goes...*checking website* The 12 Engrish Commandments And this one's for me... But not after today, I've decided. Of course, I've said that a billion times, but it's time to get healthy. I haven't had a cigarette in 4 days, and before that it was 2 days, and before that it was 3 days and before that 5 days...so I'm cutting back. Let's here it for "non-smoking pubs and restaurants"! Ah hahahahahahahaha... Now that I'm engaged, I don't have to dress up as much before we do it. Haha.. Oh dear gods, I need to get into the shower and do someting with my day. Now I'm craving Japanese food...is that normal? x Suzie

So, any takers? Haha.. Um...I'm busy...very busy at the moment. I'm moving in with my crazy ass boyfriend and going bonkers in the process. You have no idea how much stuff you have until you move...lemme just say that. It's weird, I'm upset to move from my lovely apartment in my lovely neighbourhood but I'm excited to move in with my lovely boyfriend into his lovely apartment..so it's strange. I cry too much lately..at the drop of the hat. I bailed on Sunday when we were moving things...and I mean SPLAT! out on the porch because it was wet and I went FLYING...and I bawled the whole way back to Westmount. Oh, it's tough sometimes. Anyway, I have no time to do this, I have so many other things that I have to do before 6PM tonight..sooo... I'll leave y'all with this: Why do I never tire of Surprised Pants? Haha..maybe it's because I like comfortable torches so much! And speaking of comfortable torches... Oh my god...this is too funny..
"I hope that your morning will be full of coffee smell and daydreams."

Great, now I can't seem to think of anything else. Yes, well...last night I made a bunch more icons for myself on that lovely personal avatar site, and you know what? I don't ever look like me. I do however, like to wear kimonos, chong sams, and cat ears...and have pink hair...but that's in personal avatar land. Well, and in real life too. Um...yes..

Why is it that I look like a chipmunk? I mean really? Everyone else can make something like themselves and when I try and do it, I look like I'm 5 years old..or created by Disney!!! GRRRRRRR... What do you think? The bangs aren't right..if I lower my eyes then I look all squishy, if I raise my hair...well, I don't want that big a head, thank you very much!

Although, I do enjoy hump day too...that is to say Wednesday. Haha.. You know how I don't like tomatoes, but I collect them? Well, my friends Jen and Mark enjoy Mr. Peanut..so here's something for them: It's from a series of drawings entitled "Mr. Peanut Sees the World" Haha x Suzie

It's before 9am and I've been up for a couple of hours already.  I'm having a large coffee, and I'm tapping away at the keybord.  I've got to write, go shopping, go to the post office, and get a few things sorted here.  The cleaning never seems to get done, but then again, it's prolly because I'm moving at the end of the month.  I also want to exercise, but I have no idea where to start..I suppose I could go walking today with Pogue Mahone, he's postering the Plateau today fairly early, but then that might compromise the other stuff I wanted to do today.  And Tiki Surfah has demanded (hardly) that I write a page a day, even if it kills me...so I have to do that as well. 

Ah, the joys of being unemployed.

x
Suzie

Har har..um..yeah, so I'll prolly end up writing and writing and more writing today...get a few things organised. Okay, gotta go...got work to do! x Suzie

Yes, I love roomies, and this one happens to be my best friend...although she said I wasn't her friend...that we never talked.  But I seem to recall just Wednesday last hanging out with her and then going out to L'80s night.  It was a great night...then I did laundry, I think, the next day...and as I was dying a load of black laundry, I let her put in some of her black clothes..and that makes me evil, and not a good friend, right?

Haha..

Something's afoot in Quebec City.  Or at least that's where I think the bad vibes were caught.  I wasn't there...I woulnd't know...but apparently when my mom was driving my best friend to St. Denis I got very evil and hurtful.  Now, I know that I have a sense of humour...and I know that sometimes I say things quickly...but I never, ever intentionaly try to hurt people's feelings.  I'm not like that, I don't do things like that.  But apparently on this evil car ride from Hell..or too Hell...I'm not sure...I did that.  This is what I was quoted on the phone last night...

Picture it, a lovely car ride filled with hilarity.  My mother was driving a rental car, my boyfriend (who apparently defines my personality according to my roommate) and I were sitting in the back seat...the roomie in the front.  We all piled into the car and chatted...nothing seemed wrong, except that my mother didn't turn where we told her too and we were laughing about it for a while.  The rest of the car ride was joking and whatnot...all except Elizabeth thought things were normal, dare I say it...FUN??? ARGHHHHHH!!!!!!  NO, not that!

*Look of shock and horror*

But I said something I shouldn't have...apparently...told my friend that she was like a mother.  Something that she's been telling me..."I know what it's like to have a teen-age daughter now after having lived with you."  Well, thanks for the compliment...I had no idea I looked that young!  Haha..oh, and she's obsessed with cleaning the kitty litter.  I mean, that's why she says that, because she has to do my dishes and clean up after me.  Which I admit is somewhat true...but it's hard to do things around here when they're already done.  Anyway, she liked my mom's shoes, and I made a comment..totally innocent..and now I'm evil..and she's moving out.  Sooooooooooooo weird.  I think there might be something else going on.

There is..I'm sure of it.
